VA whistleblower suggests the scandal isn't over yet
Staff at the controversial Veterans Affairs hospital in Phoenix may have continued shady scheduling practices even after   broke, according to   from CNN.   Scheduling clerk Pauline DeWenter told CNN on Monday that officials at the Phoenix VA facility continued falsifying records to hide patients who died while waiting for care. If true, the accusations mean even more patients could have died waiting for care than the original 40   in April. CNN's report came on the same day the US Office of the Special Counsel released its own  that the VA attempted to hide serious shortfalls in its health-care system. The OSC report, quoting a previous 2013 letter, indicated that the VA "has consistently failed to take responsibility for identified problems." Get our newsletter in your inbox twice a week. 